race.comment: HEALING FREQUENCY (12) was very impressive on debut here, ripping clear with a sharp turn of foot to go on and score by 3.5 lengths in good time. Straight to a BM66 here but she gets in light and draws well. Tipping she can measure right up. BOTANICAL BOY (7) is a lightly raced type who resumed with a strong run here when working home well to just miss. He'll be fitter for that and can land closer from the inside gate. Staying at 1200m is a little niggle but he can win. SUPERNIMA (2) tried hard here fresh over 1000m in very heavy going. He's much better suited to this trip and should take beating. HAPPY TIERS (8) was a strong winner two back at Bendigo, good up in grade at Moonee Valley last time. This suits and she should be very hard to hold out.
